# Playwright storageState authentication files.
#
# These JSON files contain serialised browser cookies and localStorage entries
# for pre-authenticated sessions (admin, faculty, student roles).  They are
# generated at runtime by global_setup.ts and consumed by each Playwright
# project via the `storageState` option in playwright.config.ts.
#
# Why gitignore?
#   - They may contain real session tokens / cookies — committing them would
#     expose valid credentials in the repository history.
#   - They are ephemeral: regenerated fresh on every CI run and local run.
#   - Google's hermetic test principle: auth context is created, used, and
#     discarded within a single test run; it is never persisted in source control.
#
# Files ignored:
#   admin.json   — admin role storageState
#   faculty.json — faculty role storageState
#   student.json — student role storageState
*.json
